
[1]haruspice

   HAR'USPICE,n. [L. haruspex, from specio, to view.]

   In Roman history, a person who pretended to foretell future events by
   inspecting the entrails of beasts sacrificed, or watching the
   circumstances attending their slaughter, or their manner of burning and
   the ascent of the smoke.
